WEBVTT

00:18.627 --> 00:21.064
I really admire
how you stood your ground

00:21.064 --> 00:24.154
- for your friend Malcolm X.
- He's my brother.

00:24.154 --> 00:27.114
Malcolm and Che are gonna be
speaking at the United Nations.

00:27.114 --> 00:28.419
That's just
between me and you.

00:28.419 --> 00:29.681
I don't want nothing
to happen to Malcolm.

00:29.681 --> 00:32.162
I would never betray
your confidence.

00:32.162 --> 00:34.338
Chin Gigante put
a hit out on me--

00:34.338 --> 00:36.688
something he couldn't have done
without your fuckin' approval.

00:36.688 --> 00:38.864
I told Fineman
you tried to fuck me.

00:38.864 --> 00:40.388
- Ohh.
- I'm sorry.

00:40.388 --> 00:44.131
I got you into this mess.
I'll get you out.

00:44.131 --> 00:46.089
One of those bosses
tried to have me killed.

00:46.089 --> 00:49.397
We figure out who that was,
use it as leverage.

00:49.397 --> 00:50.789
Oh!

00:50.789 --> 00:52.530
Who'd you get to put
the hit out on me?

00:52.530 --> 00:54.576
Gambino? Lucchese?

00:54.576 --> 00:56.839
What the fuck does that
have to do with me?

00:56.839 --> 00:59.755
He knows, Tommy.
He knows everything.

00:59.755 --> 01:03.367
You not only put a hit out
on a boss's daughter,

01:03.367 --> 01:05.195
you also fucked his wife.

01:05.195 --> 01:10.113
Word gets out, you don't make it
past breakfast tomorrow.

01:10.113 --> 01:11.593
<i>I spoke with Sister Marny,</i>

01:11.593 --> 01:13.334
<i>made her think
I was on her side.</i>

01:13.334 --> 01:17.251
<i>And she pointed me to
Mosque Number 25 in Newark,</i>

01:17.251 --> 01:19.601
<i>where Brother Clyde
and Sister Sondra</i>

01:19.601 --> 01:23.518
are crafting a plan
to kill you, Malcolm.

01:23.518 --> 01:25.650
Why are you doing all this?
Why risk your life?

01:25.650 --> 01:30.351
I wanted to redeem myself
through deed and not word.

01:30.351 --> 01:33.397
You want me to convince Lillian
to go away with her husband,

01:33.397 --> 01:35.530
and you won't tell me why?

01:35.530 --> 01:37.227
Archie's been doing
some work for me.

01:37.227 --> 01:39.316
And there's some people
that think

01:39.316 --> 01:41.405
that he might be talking
to the Feds.

01:41.405 --> 01:42.580
They could be right.

01:42.580 --> 01:44.669
Ellsworth, what have you
gotten him into?

01:47.759 --> 01:50.153
Oh!

01:50.153 --> 01:52.590
God! Archie! Archie!

01:52.590 --> 01:54.244
Archie Gaines--
the classified informant!

01:54.244 --> 01:56.420
You left him wide-ass open!

01:56.420 --> 01:59.423
I have no idea
who Archie Gaines is.

01:59.423 --> 02:02.513
And there's a much bigger game
being played here.

02:02.513 --> 02:04.863
It's about the fate
of this country.

02:04.863 --> 02:07.257
<i>I should've smelled
a rat sooner myself.</i>

02:07.257 --> 02:08.693
What?

02:08.693 --> 02:10.173
You were the only one
I told about Malcolm

02:10.173 --> 02:12.610
speaking with Che
at the United Nations.

02:12.610 --> 02:15.744
Do you understand
what your friend is doing?

02:15.744 --> 02:17.702
Partnering with Che Guevara,
a man who wants to have

02:17.702 --> 02:20.183
communist revolutions
all over the world.

02:20.183 --> 02:21.619
The buddy-buddy shit
with this Malcolm character

02:21.619 --> 02:23.969
is gonna destroy your business,
if not your life.

02:23.969 --> 02:28.191
If I get touched,
Operation Mongoose goes public.

02:28.191 --> 02:31.760
I'm sorry, brother.
I don't trust you anymore.

02:31.760 --> 02:34.154
This partnership is over.

02:36.678 --> 02:37.766
What's that?

02:47.645 --> 02:50.692
<i>Ernesto Che Guevara,
Cuba's Minister of Industry,</i>

02:50.692 --> 02:52.346
<i>arrived in New York
this morning,</i>

02:52.346 --> 02:53.956
<i>set to address
the United Nations</i>

02:53.956 --> 02:55.827
<i>General Assembly this week.</i>

02:55.827 --> 02:57.916
<i>It's rumored
that he may be accompanied</i>

02:57.916 --> 03:01.920
<i>by Black militant nationalist
Malcolm El Shabazz,</i>

03:01.920 --> 03:04.488
<i>better known as Malcolm X.</i>

03:04.488 --> 03:06.621
<i>Their appearance has been
deemed controversial</i>

03:06.621 --> 03:07.883
<i>and even dangerous,</i>

03:07.883 --> 03:09.624
<i>as U.S. officials worry</i>

03:09.624 --> 03:11.669
<i>that these radicals
aim to perpetuate</i>

03:11.669 --> 03:15.586
<i>the spread of communism
from the Soviet Union and Cuba.</i>

03:15.586 --> 03:17.588
You'd be a fool
to make that speech.

03:17.588 --> 03:18.328
<i>...the spread of communism...</i>

03:18.328 --> 03:19.677
And why is that?

03:19.677 --> 03:20.722
<i>...in other parts
of the world...</i>

03:20.722 --> 03:22.811
The CIA, the FBI.

03:22.811 --> 03:24.334
The NOI, the KKK.

03:24.334 --> 03:27.337
It's all part of
the wallpaper now, brother.

03:27.337 --> 03:29.687
I didn't work so hard
to protect your ass

03:29.687 --> 03:30.819
to watch you blow it.

03:30.819 --> 03:32.037
<i>♪ Right now</i>

03:32.037 --> 03:33.952
You haven't touched
your food.

03:33.952 --> 03:36.868
<i>♪ I know it's late</i>

03:36.868 --> 03:41.264
A man stops eating
when his mind eats <i>him.</i>

03:41.264 --> 03:43.353
Talk to me, brother.

03:43.353 --> 03:45.268
I lost Mayme.

03:45.268 --> 03:46.443
I'm sorry to hear that.

03:46.443 --> 03:47.575
<i>♪ Please steal away</i>

03:47.575 --> 03:49.533
What was the trouble?

03:49.533 --> 03:54.712
<i>♪ Now, don't start thinkin'</i>

03:54.712 --> 03:57.324
I had to start
dealing narcotics again.

03:57.324 --> 04:00.936
Things got... complicated.

04:00.936 --> 04:04.331
One of our friends
was laundering money.

04:04.331 --> 04:05.984
Got caught
in the crossfire.

04:05.984 --> 04:07.638
<i>♪ I know it's late</i>

04:07.638 --> 04:09.858
<i>♪ Whoa, I can't wait</i>

04:09.858 --> 04:12.295
Bumpy, that's actually
part of the reason

04:12.295 --> 04:14.079
I asked you here to breakfast.

04:14.079 --> 04:16.908
Now, I'm sorry about Mayme.

04:16.908 --> 04:19.041
I'm sure your love
for one another

04:19.041 --> 04:21.870
will overcome these obstacles.

04:23.045 --> 04:26.744
But I believe it's time for you
to dismiss the security detail.

04:28.006 --> 04:29.312
No.

04:31.445 --> 04:33.751
Are you serious?

04:33.751 --> 04:36.841
We have United Nations security
as we prepare to speak.

04:36.841 --> 04:40.323
It just doesn't work to have
ex-felons as part of the detail.

04:40.323 --> 04:41.977
I'm sorry.

04:45.023 --> 04:49.593
I'm forever grateful to you
for protecting my family and me.

04:51.900 --> 04:54.946
But a man can't help anyone...

04:54.946 --> 04:57.384
'til his own house is in order.

05:01.605 --> 05:03.564
Don't let your home
collapse around you.

05:03.564 --> 05:06.349
Rebuild.

05:06.349 --> 05:09.787
You haven't worked this hard
for your own ass to blow it.

05:14.662 --> 05:16.054
It takes
a lot of ingenuity

05:16.054 --> 05:17.926
to kill two men at once,

05:17.926 --> 05:19.667
but I think we've got
the perfect solution.

05:21.190 --> 05:24.019
An M-20? Where the fuck
did you get this?

05:24.019 --> 05:27.457
23rd and 10th.
Army Surplus store.

05:27.457 --> 05:28.980
You bought this
in a store?

05:28.980 --> 05:30.460
Well, that's the beauty.

05:30.460 --> 05:32.636
Any schmo off the street
can walk in and buy one.

05:32.636 --> 05:34.943
CIA--
plausible deniability.

05:40.165 --> 05:42.733
Come with me.

05:42.733 --> 05:44.692
This is
a demonstration model,

05:44.692 --> 05:46.911
a fifth as powerful
as the one we'll repurpose.

05:46.911 --> 05:50.959
Now, the shell is loaded
with Composition B.

05:50.959 --> 05:55.006
If it hits, anything
within 50 feet is charcoal.

05:55.006 --> 05:57.444
Che Guevara, Malcolm X.

05:57.444 --> 05:59.533
Two commies, one stone.

